Module com.mc.InventorySystem
Package com.mc.controller

Class ModifyPartController

java.lang.Object
com.mc.controller.ModifyPartController
public class ModifyPartController extends Object
The controller class for the Modify Part screen. It handles user input and updates the Part data in the Inventory system accordingly. It also provides error checking for user input and displays error messages when necessary.
Author:
Michael Cassidy

  • Method Details

    • initialize

      private void initialize()
      This method is called by JavaFX after the FXML file has been loaded and the root node has been processed. It initializes the in-house and outsourced radio buttons and sets the appropriate label for the text field based on the currently selected radio button.

    • setPart

      Parameters:
      part - The part to be modified
      index - The index of the selected part in the table

    • onActionSave

      private void onActionSave(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws IOException
      Handles the functionality of the Modify Part screen. Allows the user to modify an existing part and saves the changes to the inventory. Validates user input to ensure correct formatting and data types are used. Displays error messages to the user if input is not valid.
      Parameters:
      event - The event that triggers the method.
      Throws:
      IOException - if an error occurs while loading the main menu screen.

    • onActionInHouse

      private void onActionInHouse(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Event handler for when the in-house radio button is selected. Sets the dynamic label to "Machine ID".

    • onActionOutsourced

      private void onActionOutsourced(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
